<TITLE> 50 students sued over Sunday's violence </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Gazipur, May 11 (bdnews24.com)  A case was filed on Tuesday against students of Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman Agricultural University in Gazipur over Sunday's attack, vandalism and arson. Joydevpur police chief Abdur Rashid said the case accused some 50 students, eight of whom were named. Anwarul Kabir Chowdhury, security officer of the university, lodged the case. The eight accused areMonjur Rahman Monju, Md Tareq Rahman, Ridwanul Alam, Peter Saikat, Md Rashed Chowdhury, Mainuddin Ahmed, Md Helal Uddin and Benzir Ahmed. Autorities on Sunday shut down the university. Male students had left the dormitories at night and the female on Monday morning. bdnews24.com Gazipur correspondent had reported that the university expelled four students of the agriculture faculty on May 4 for failing to attain the minimum required CGPA of 2.5. Students of the faculty demonstrated from noon to 8pm on Thursday, boycotted classes, staged sit-in and submitted a memorandum to the vice-chancellor demanding withdrawal of the decision. On Sunday, the agitating students staged further demonstration and a sit-in in front of the main entrance. Some 10 students fell sick due to the extreme heat. Proctor Jalal Uddin had said that the demonstrators were further agitated by this incident and vandalised the bank building and wrecked the glasses of various faculty buildings and a bus at around 9pm. Police intervened to bring the situation under control. bdne
